casebody.data:
First Department,

January, 1945.

(January 10, 1945.) Consolidated Edison Company of New York, Inc., v. Walter J. Salmon et al.

Motion for leave to appeal to the Court of Appeals or for a reargument and for a stay denied, with ten dollars costs. [See ante, p. 898.] Present — Martin, P. J., Townley, Glennon and Dore, JJ.
